.TH "SWAYIMG" "1" "2026-02-28" "swayimg" "Swayimg manual"
.SH NAME
.PP
swayimg - image viewer for Wayland display servers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\fBswayimg\fR [OPTIONS]... [FILE]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
If no input files or directories are specified, the viewer will try to read all
files in the current directory.
.PP
Use '-' as FILE to read image data from stdin.
.PP
Use prefix \fBexec://\fR to get image data from stdout printed by external command.
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Mandatory arguments to long options are mandatory for short options too.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.IP "\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR"
Display help message and exit.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.IP "\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR"
Display version information and list of supported image formats.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.IP "\fB\-g\fR, \fB\-\-gallery\fR"
Start in gallery mode.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.IP "\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-slideshow\fR"
Start in slide show mode.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.IP "\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-from\-file\fR=\fIFILE\fR"
Load file list from specified \fIFILE\fR.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.IP "\fB\-P\fR, \fB\-\-position\fR=\fIXxY\fR"
Set initial position of the window (Sway/Hyperland only).
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.IP "\fB\-S\fR, \fB\-\-size\fR=\fIWxH\fR"
Set initial size of the window.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.IP "\fB\-F\fR, \fB\-\-fullscreen\fR"
Start in full-screen mode.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.IP "\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-class\fR=\fIAPPID\fR"
Set window class (application id).
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.IP "\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-config\fR=\fIFILE\fR"
Load config specified \fIFILE\fR.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.IP "\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR"
Enable verbose output.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH SWAY/HYPRLAND INTEGRATION
.PP
This mode provides some features such as setting the window position and
getting the workspace layout.
The application creates an "overlay" above the currently active
window, which gives the illusion that the image is opened directly inside
the terminal window.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.IP "\fISWAYSOCK\fR"
Path to the socket file used for Sway IPC.
.IP "\fIHYPRLAND_INSTANCE_SIGNATURE\fR, \fIXDG_RUNTIME_DIR\fR"
Path to the socket file used for Hyprland IPC.
.IP "\fIXDG_CONFIG_HOME\fR, \fIXDG_CONFIG_DIRS\fR, \fIHOME\fR"
Prefix of the path to default application config file.
.IP "\fISHELL\fR"
Shell for executing an external command and loading an image from stdout.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH SIGNALS
.IP "\fISIGUSR1\fR, \fISIGUSR2\fR"
Perform the actions specified in the config file.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH EXIT STATUS
The exit status is 0 if the program completed successfully and 1 if an
error occurred. Other codes can be specified via config file.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH BUGS
.PP
For suggestions, comments, bug reports, etc. visit the project homepage
https://github.com/artemsen/swayimg.
